On 1/6/06, Jan Engelhardt <jengelh@linux01.gwdg.de> wrote:
> >> >                         printk(space == 0 ? "     " : "\n");
> >> >                         space = !space;
> >>
> >> readability ?
> >
> >Well, if I were going for _un_readability I'd have suggested:
> >
> >        printk(space = !space ? "     " : "\n");
>
> Anyone voting for "\t" instead of "     "?
Sure: if you use '\t' then you can do:
printk("%c", 9+space++);
space &= 1;
No branches ;)
